      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, i thought blueberries were supposed to like acidic soil specifically? i read somewhere that if the pH gets too high, the iron basically gets \"locked\" in the soil and the roots can't grab it even if it's right there. can you go into a bit more detail on the actual chemistry of how that works? like how the ions interact with the soil and the roots?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
